&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clarity over completeness.&lt;/strong&gt; You know how to synthesize a complex program into what actually matters — for the working team and for leadership — without losing the thread.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influence without authority.&lt;/strong&gt; You&#39;ve driven outcomes across teams that don&#39;t report to you, and you&#39;ve done it by building trust, not just by asking nicely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure as a service.&lt;/strong&gt; You bring frameworks and operating rhythms because they genuinely help people do better work — not because they look good in a slide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bias for momentum.&lt;/strong&gt; You identify blockers early and move fast to clear them. You don&#39;t wait for a perfect plan to start making progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curiosity about the business.&lt;/strong&gt; You want to understand why the programs you&#39;re running matter, not just how to keep them on track.&lt;/p&gt;
